1
00:00:42,230 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:48,779
So I'm warning you.

3
00:00:48,862 --> 00:00:50,781
Listen carefully to what I'm about to say.

4
00:00:50,864 --> 00:00:52,240
I'm about to do something,

5
00:00:52,324 --> 00:00:53,992
so if you want to run, now's your chance.

6
00:00:54,076 --> 00:00:55,327
I'll give you three seconds.

7
00:00:55,410 --> 00:00:56,328
One.

8
00:00:58,538 --> 00:00:59,623
Two.

9
00:01:00,499 --> 00:01:01,667
Three.

10
00:01:22,854 --> 00:01:24,648
<i>Shin Seo-ri, you're in trouble.</i>

11
00:01:26,066 --> 00:01:27,067
<i>Truth is,</i>

12
00:01:27,901 --> 00:01:29,486
<i>I never had any intention</i>

13
00:01:30,654 --> 00:01:31,822
<i>of letting you go.</i>

14
00:01:31,905 --> 00:01:33,657
You grabbed me first.

15
00:01:35,492 --> 00:01:36,910
<i>So now,</i>

16
00:01:36,993 --> 00:01:39,454
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

17
00:01:58,557 --> 00:02:00,225
What might this be?

18
00:02:00,308 --> 00:02:02,060
It is a <i>Cheomjado</i> from Qing.

19
00:02:03,895 --> 00:02:06,857
A gift for my dearest companion.

20
00:02:10,068 --> 00:02:11,862
If you wished to give a gift,

21
00:02:12,612 --> 00:02:14,322
you should have brought sweets.

22
00:02:14,406 --> 00:02:16,032
Why a silver dagger?

23
00:02:16,116 --> 00:02:17,325
So…

24
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:19,953
is it not to your liking at all?

25
00:02:20,036 --> 00:02:21,663
What is a silver dagger?

26
00:02:21,747 --> 00:02:23,957
It is a dagger meant
for women's self-defense,

27
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,209
but it is truly only used
to end one's life.

28
00:02:26,293 --> 00:02:28,253
Since I will never use it for that,

29
00:02:28,336 --> 00:02:30,505
I shall just use it to peel chestnuts.

30
00:02:32,758 --> 00:02:33,842
Are you

31
00:02:33,925 --> 00:02:36,261
lecturing me for giving you a gift?

32
00:02:36,344 --> 00:02:38,555
Are you not afraid of me?

33
00:02:38,638 --> 00:02:40,974
Have I not told you before?

34
00:02:41,057 --> 00:02:42,976
I am not frightened in the least.

35
00:02:43,643 --> 00:02:45,312
That is why I do not understand

36
00:02:45,395 --> 00:02:47,314
why such hideous rumors circulate.

37
00:02:49,232 --> 00:02:50,400
There is

38
00:02:51,401 --> 00:02:53,111
a secret behind those rumors.

39
00:02:53,195 --> 00:02:54,446
Shall I tell you?

40
00:02:54,529 --> 00:02:57,783
Those rumors of the Blind Goblin
and the Ghost Prince…

41
00:02:59,701 --> 00:03:01,495
I started them.

42
00:03:01,578 --> 00:03:03,038
But why…

43
00:03:03,914 --> 00:03:05,457
The more hideous the rumors,

44
00:03:05,957 --> 00:03:07,959
the better they shield me.

45
00:03:08,043 --> 00:03:09,461
They keep anyone

46
00:03:09,544 --> 00:03:11,755
from daring to come near me.

47
00:03:13,465 --> 00:03:15,133
But now we have trouble afoot.

48
00:03:16,593 --> 00:03:18,929
You have already come too close,

49
00:03:19,596 --> 00:03:21,890
and you even know all about my secret.

50
00:03:21,973 --> 00:03:24,059
What shall I do with you now?

51
00:03:29,731 --> 00:03:31,441
Shall I kill you?

52
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:35,362
Or let you live?

53
00:03:40,408 --> 00:03:41,451
Never mind.

54
00:03:41,952 --> 00:03:44,996
My only companion might turn
her blade against me,

55
00:03:45,497 --> 00:03:47,207
so I must be careful.

56
00:04:24,202 --> 00:04:26,121
<i>Could the full moon be to blame?</i>

57
00:04:28,331 --> 00:04:30,458
Such strange memories rise to the surface.

58
00:04:34,004 --> 00:04:36,298
Or perhaps that haughty voice is to blame?

59
00:04:37,966 --> 00:04:39,634
What's wrong with my voice?

60
00:04:41,595 --> 00:04:43,221
Music to your ears?

61
00:04:43,305 --> 00:04:45,015
I get that a lot.

62
00:04:45,098 --> 00:04:48,268
Women have said it's
dreamy like some ASMR boyfriend…

63
00:04:49,185 --> 00:04:51,354
Wait, what? What memories?

64
00:04:51,438 --> 00:04:53,398
-Don't tell me they're of an ex.
-You.

65
00:04:54,024 --> 00:04:56,484
You must cease your endless prattling.

66
00:04:57,027 --> 00:04:58,278
I cannot think straight.

67
00:04:58,361 --> 00:05:00,614
Let me make this clear now.
I'm the super jealous type.

68
00:05:00,697 --> 00:05:02,866
I won't tolerate any
of that cliché first love nonsense.

69
00:05:02,949 --> 00:05:04,659
Pining for another guy around me?

70
00:05:04,743 --> 00:05:07,078
I absolutely despise stuff like that.
I really do.

71
00:05:07,162 --> 00:05:09,748
Perhaps the aura of the full moon

72
00:05:09,831 --> 00:05:11,791
is stirring my heart?

73
00:05:13,001 --> 00:05:16,087
"The bright moon rises,
revealing my beautiful love."

74
00:05:16,171 --> 00:05:18,089
"It tenderly stirs and blooms."

75
00:05:18,173 --> 00:05:20,467
"My heart aches in longing."

76
00:05:20,550 --> 00:05:22,677
What are you getting
all philosophical for?

77
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:25,347
If it's beautiful, why does it ache?

78
00:05:32,771 --> 00:05:35,440
I see you bear
the face of a sinner as well.

79
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:39,027
You will surely end up breaking
many a maiden's heart.

80
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:41,071
That face is destined for high treason.

81
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:45,116
You're completely smitten.

82
00:06:01,216 --> 00:06:03,635
No wonder you make hearts ache.

83
00:06:15,814 --> 00:06:18,608
Be honest. You were never
"romantically impotent," were you?

84
00:06:18,692 --> 00:06:21,528
You're a pro, right? Busted.

85
00:06:21,611 --> 00:06:23,822
You toyed with me like I was some yo-yo.

86
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:31,788
What the…

87
00:06:31,871 --> 00:06:33,873
So you're just going to fall asleep now?

88
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:39,462
Meanwhile, my heart feels like
it's about to burst.

89
00:06:40,088 --> 00:06:41,506
Damn it.

90
00:06:49,723 --> 00:06:51,016
She's really asleep.

91
00:07:12,996 --> 00:07:17,625
EPISODE 7
THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON

92
00:07:26,843 --> 00:07:29,012
<i>Once a gloomy day passes,</i>

93
00:07:29,095 --> 00:07:32,098
<i>a pleasant new sun is bound to rise.</i>

94
00:07:32,182 --> 00:07:34,017
<i>I have the warm sunlight,</i>

95
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:36,061
<i>and I am wrapped</i>

96
00:07:36,144 --> 00:07:39,481
<i>in these damp silk sheets.</i>

97
00:07:40,857 --> 00:07:41,733
<i>Hold on.</i>

98
00:07:42,776 --> 00:07:44,235
<i>Why does this…</i>

99
00:07:56,915 --> 00:07:59,042
Have I transcended time and space again?

100
00:08:08,593 --> 00:08:10,887
Jeez. I guess I dozed off.

101
00:08:11,721 --> 00:08:13,640
Where has she gone now?

102
00:08:14,849 --> 00:08:16,226
Did she just abandon me here?

103
00:08:22,273 --> 00:08:23,525
Damn it.

104
00:08:25,235 --> 00:08:26,528
Shin Seo-ri.

105
00:08:27,654 --> 00:08:29,072
Shin Seo-ri!

106
00:08:36,287 --> 00:08:37,372
Seo-ri, are you nuts?

107
00:08:37,455 --> 00:08:39,499
-What are you doing?
-You tell me!

108
00:08:39,582 --> 00:08:41,167
Swim without a plan, and you'll drown!

109
00:08:41,251 --> 00:08:43,962
Swim where? Where are we?

110
00:08:44,045 --> 00:08:45,421
-You don't know?
-I do not.

111
00:08:45,505 --> 00:08:46,673
Why not? We came here together.

112
00:08:46,756 --> 00:08:48,591
I came here with you?

113
00:08:48,675 --> 00:08:50,301
I have no memory of that.

114
00:08:51,427 --> 00:08:52,512
Wait, you blacked out?

115
00:08:53,888 --> 00:08:55,265
Where are we?

116
00:09:04,607 --> 00:09:07,068
Yeah. Not a single soul in sight.

117
00:09:07,152 --> 00:09:08,361
Like a deserted island.

118
00:09:13,074 --> 00:09:14,576
Surely you jest.

119
00:09:29,632 --> 00:09:30,884
<i>A deserted island?</i>

120
00:09:32,177 --> 00:09:34,679
Why a deserted island, all of a sudden?

121
00:09:34,762 --> 00:09:36,973
The app tracked him to one
ten minutes ago.

122
00:09:37,056 --> 00:09:38,725
App? You're tracking his phone?

123
00:09:39,475 --> 00:09:41,686
Ms. Kim, how can you be so clueless?

124
00:09:41,769 --> 00:09:43,146
A competent aide

125
00:09:43,229 --> 00:09:45,815
installs a tracking app
on their boss's phone.

126
00:09:45,899 --> 00:09:47,317
That's standard.

127
00:09:49,402 --> 00:09:53,489
LOVE RADAR LOCATION TRACKING
MR. CHA

128
00:09:58,411 --> 00:09:59,871
I have not committed any sins.

129
00:09:59,954 --> 00:10:01,748
Why have I been exiled here?

130
00:10:01,831 --> 00:10:03,791
No, I must pull myself together.

131
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:06,794
If I keep my wits about me,
I will find a way.

132
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:08,671
Cha Se-gye!

133
00:10:08,755 --> 00:10:10,298
Do you know how to dive?

134
00:10:10,381 --> 00:10:11,883
Swim? No, I sink like a stone.

135
00:10:11,966 --> 00:10:13,551
Then let us light a fire for smoke--

136
00:10:13,635 --> 00:10:15,303
No lighter. I quit smoking.

137
00:10:15,386 --> 00:10:16,346
Right, our phones!

138
00:10:16,429 --> 00:10:17,555
If we call for help--

139
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:19,224
My battery's dead.

140
00:10:19,307 --> 00:10:21,893
We have to do something.
You cannot just say no to everything.

141
00:10:21,976 --> 00:10:23,686
There's nothing we can do.

142
00:10:24,938 --> 00:10:25,980
We live here now.

143
00:10:26,064 --> 00:10:27,523
That is nonsense.

144
00:10:27,607 --> 00:10:28,483
How can we live here?

145
00:10:29,359 --> 00:10:32,487
We're a man and a woman trapped alone
on a deserted island. What can we do?

146
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:35,156
We'll just have to make
a cozy little life together.

147
00:10:36,115 --> 00:10:36,991
How romantic.

148
00:10:37,075 --> 00:10:38,493
Our very own Mont Saint-Michel.

149
00:10:41,579 --> 00:10:43,248
So are we official now?

150
00:10:43,331 --> 00:10:45,792
If you'd like,
you can call me your husband.

151
00:10:48,419 --> 00:10:49,921
Husband, my foot.

152
00:10:57,512 --> 00:10:58,972
<i>You grabbed me first.</i>

153
00:11:08,523 --> 00:11:09,774
<i>What did I do last night?</i>

154
00:11:30,753 --> 00:11:34,215
<i>-On to Ieo Island</i>
<i>-On to Ieo Island</i>

155
00:11:34,299 --> 00:11:37,051
<i>-On to Ieo Island</i>
<i>-On to Ieo Island</i>

156
00:11:37,135 --> 00:11:39,429
<i>-Strike, strike</i>
<i>-Strike, strike</i>

157
00:11:39,512 --> 00:11:41,180
<i>-Row, pull</i>
<i>-Row, pull</i>

158
00:11:41,264 --> 00:11:42,307
Wait.

159
00:11:42,390 --> 00:11:43,641
Is that…

160
00:11:43,725 --> 00:11:45,643
Yeah, that's Mount Halla.

161
00:11:46,269 --> 00:11:47,770
Why is it over there?

162
00:11:47,854 --> 00:11:49,480
You came out here

163
00:11:49,564 --> 00:11:51,566
at low tide last night and got trapped.

164
00:11:51,649 --> 00:11:53,484
If it weren't for us,

165
00:11:53,568 --> 00:11:55,820
you'd be stuck here until evening.

166
00:12:00,992 --> 00:12:02,660
Did you enjoy making a fool out of me?

167
00:12:02,744 --> 00:12:04,203
You said it was utterly deserted.

168
00:12:06,789 --> 00:12:10,126
It is a deserted island.
One that's a stone's throw from Jeju.

169
00:12:10,209 --> 00:12:11,669
Then you should have told me.

170
00:12:11,753 --> 00:12:12,628
We both drank last night,

171
00:12:12,712 --> 00:12:14,672
yet I'm the only one
who made a fool of myself.

172
00:12:14,756 --> 00:12:16,049
I didn't drink.

173
00:12:16,132 --> 00:12:17,091
You drank it all.

174
00:12:17,175 --> 00:12:19,052
I saw you drink. You chugged it all down.

175
00:12:19,135 --> 00:12:21,971
I was just faking it.
It was fun being the only sober one.

176
00:12:22,055 --> 00:12:24,599
Am I some court jester
here to entertain you?

177
00:12:24,682 --> 00:12:25,558
So,

178
00:12:25,641 --> 00:12:27,435
did you enjoy your time on Seogeon Island?

179
00:12:27,518 --> 00:12:30,271
I hope you took it nice and slow
through the night.

180
00:12:31,522 --> 00:12:33,441
Do you not understand?

181
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:36,319
They're still young enough
to be sharing steamy nights.

182
00:12:36,402 --> 00:12:38,404
Must be nice to be that young.

183
00:12:38,488 --> 00:12:40,281
-Steamy night.
-"Steamy night"?

184
00:12:40,365 --> 00:12:42,658
My goodness. Look at that man's face.

185
00:12:42,742 --> 00:12:45,328
Flushed like he just crawled out
of a chestnut roaster.

186
00:12:45,912 --> 00:12:48,331
-His face is beet red.
-Yeah.

187
00:12:48,414 --> 00:12:49,707
He looks fresh out of a dive.

188
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:50,666
Gosh.

189
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,752
Do you understand
what those grannies are saying?

190
00:12:52,835 --> 00:12:55,755
I'm not sure,
but it definitely sounds like dirty talk.

191
00:12:56,381 --> 00:12:57,757
"Dirty talk"?

192
00:12:58,591 --> 00:13:00,551
They are giving us a weird look.

193
00:13:00,635 --> 00:13:03,388
As if I were just caught
stealing some roasted chestnuts.

194
00:13:03,471 --> 00:13:04,389
Do not talk to them.

195
00:13:04,472 --> 00:13:07,475
It sounds like
"roasted chestnuts" may be a euphemism.

196
00:13:07,558 --> 00:13:10,478
No, they look at me as if I were
a minx who stole her husband.

197
00:13:10,561 --> 00:13:11,687
Do not even make eye contact.

198
00:13:11,771 --> 00:13:12,647
-Sister.
-Yeah?

199
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:14,690
That young lady…

200
00:13:14,774 --> 00:13:16,901
I think I've seen her somewhere.

201
00:13:16,984 --> 00:13:20,238
She looks strangely familiar.

202
00:13:20,321 --> 00:13:21,197
Yeah.

203
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,448
Where have we seen her?

204
00:13:22,532 --> 00:13:24,075
-Yeah, I wonder.
-Where was it?

205
00:13:24,158 --> 00:13:26,035
One, two, three.

206
00:13:26,119 --> 00:13:29,122
Gosh. You know,
she's totally addicted to YouTube Shorts.

207
00:13:29,205 --> 00:13:32,625
How did you ever recognize
the Kim Du-han girl right away?

208
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:34,794
I know, right? Heart!

209
00:13:37,046 --> 00:13:38,756
Oh my, is this young lady really

210
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,091
the Kim Du-han girl?

211
00:13:40,174 --> 00:13:41,342
Yes, she is.

212
00:13:41,426 --> 00:13:42,718
Goodness me.

213
00:13:43,845 --> 00:13:45,555
"Kim Du-han"?

214
00:13:48,349 --> 00:13:50,768
-But this is…
-Oysters, abalone. Wild-caught.

215
00:13:51,978 --> 00:13:53,312
Wild-caught?

216
00:13:53,396 --> 00:13:55,481
Why don't you just eat it now?

217
00:13:55,565 --> 00:13:57,442
-Yeah, you should!
-Let's go.

218
00:13:57,525 --> 00:13:59,318
-Go ahead.
-Let's go.

219
00:13:59,402 --> 00:14:01,154
Here, sit right here.

220
00:14:01,654 --> 00:14:03,030
Sit right here.

221
00:14:03,114 --> 00:14:04,657
-Right there. Gosh.
-Sit right here.

222
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:05,741
What about me?

223
00:14:06,868 --> 00:14:09,662
Wait. She was also here yesterday.

224
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:12,999
But didn't Mr. Cha drink yesterday?

225
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,209
And he drove…

226
00:14:15,293 --> 00:14:16,252
DUI.

227
00:14:17,795 --> 00:14:19,964
Please keep this confidential for now.

228
00:14:20,047 --> 00:14:21,048
We'd appreciate it.

229
00:14:21,716 --> 00:14:22,633
Yes. Sure.

230
00:14:28,973 --> 00:14:30,183
CEO CHA SE-GYE

231
00:14:31,184 --> 00:14:32,059
Sir.

232
00:14:35,938 --> 00:14:38,441
I know you wanted a romantic getaway,
but you've crossed the line.

233
00:14:38,524 --> 00:14:41,068
A DUI these days will ruin you.

234
00:14:41,152 --> 00:14:42,570
What do you mean, a DUI?

235
00:14:42,653 --> 00:14:44,155
CCTV does not lie.
The evidence is stacked.

236
00:14:44,238 --> 00:14:45,448
You need to calm down, Mr. Son.

237
00:14:45,531 --> 00:14:47,450
I didn't drink a single drop of alcohol.

238
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:49,160
If you are that scared, let me.

239
00:14:49,243 --> 00:14:51,996
-Hand it over.
-Who says I'm scared?

240
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:55,958
<i>I switched the cups right</i>
<i>in front of everyone, but no one noticed.</i>

241
00:14:56,042 --> 00:14:58,336
My hands are pretty fast, though.

242
00:15:00,254 --> 00:15:01,297
Hey.

243
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:04,592
Why say yes to all this and lug it back
when you could just buy it in Seoul?

244
00:15:04,675 --> 00:15:07,136
These are tribute gifts
straight from my fan.

245
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:09,055
Do not compare this to store-bought.

246
00:15:09,931 --> 00:15:11,015
"Tribute gifts"? As if.

247
00:15:11,098 --> 00:15:12,934
You sure do love your fans.

248
00:15:13,017 --> 00:15:15,436
Sir, it's almost time for your flight.

249
00:15:18,731 --> 00:15:21,150
I'm off to Seoul. Good luck shooting.

250
00:15:21,234 --> 00:15:22,443
Your manager is on his way.

251
00:15:22,527 --> 00:15:23,986
Wait right here. Don't go anywhere.

252
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:25,321
What am I, a kid?

253
00:15:25,404 --> 00:15:26,614
Just go.

254
00:15:28,616 --> 00:15:30,159
You better remember.

255
00:15:31,077 --> 00:15:33,663
Don't even think
about playing the blacked-out card.

256
00:15:33,746 --> 00:15:35,164
And you can forget about running.

257
00:15:35,248 --> 00:15:37,917
You will never be able
to take back what happened yesterday.

258
00:15:41,796 --> 00:15:43,548
As if anything happened yesterday.

259
00:15:43,631 --> 00:15:44,840
Are you threatening me?

260
00:15:44,924 --> 00:15:46,300
No, I'm locking you down.

261
00:15:46,842 --> 00:15:49,136
You're mine whether you like it or not.

262
00:15:56,561 --> 00:15:58,187
I do not belong to anyone.

263
00:16:01,524 --> 00:16:03,943
Mochang Group has agreed
to a business partnership

264
00:16:04,026 --> 00:16:05,945
for the resort development.

265
00:16:07,154 --> 00:16:08,906
CHAIL PROPERTIES AND MOCHANG LIFE
SIGN RESORT DEVELOPMENT MOU

266
00:16:09,865 --> 00:16:11,450
<i>I heard about you and Se-gye.</i>

267
00:16:11,534 --> 00:16:13,578
I didn't realize you were ready
to settle down.

268
00:16:13,661 --> 00:16:14,787
I was a bit surprised.

269
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:16,455
I wasn't,

270
00:16:16,539 --> 00:16:17,999
but I changed my mind.

271
00:16:18,082 --> 00:16:19,000
After meeting Se-gye.

272
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:22,003
That unpredictable free spirit of his

273
00:16:22,086 --> 00:16:24,338
was quite refreshing, for a change.

274
00:16:27,341 --> 00:16:30,469
As she said,
the blind date must have gone well.

275
00:16:30,553 --> 00:16:32,555
Uncle managed to pull off a clever move…

276
00:16:33,431 --> 00:16:34,557
for a change.

277
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,475
There is speculation
that marriage is expected

278
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:37,685
to formalize this alliance.

279
00:16:37,768 --> 00:16:38,853
We can't let that happen.

280
00:16:38,936 --> 00:16:41,063
Get me the VIP number for Mochang.

281
00:16:41,147 --> 00:16:44,358
She is really something else.
That Mo Tae-hee.

282
00:16:44,442 --> 00:16:47,612
I heard she made a name for herself
with a startup overseas.

283
00:16:48,279 --> 00:16:50,865
A solid background, good looks…

284
00:16:50,948 --> 00:16:53,367
Her résumé is exactly
what Father would love.

285
00:16:53,451 --> 00:16:54,535
Exactly.

286
00:16:54,619 --> 00:16:56,871
We need to stay on our guard.

287
00:16:56,954 --> 00:16:59,874
Se-gye alone is already
giving me a massive headache.

288
00:16:59,957 --> 00:17:02,293
You let a thing like that into the house,

289
00:17:02,376 --> 00:17:04,837
and we'll both be dead in the water.

290
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:08,215
Hello.

291
00:17:08,299 --> 00:17:09,175
-Hi.
-Hello.

292
00:17:09,258 --> 00:17:10,718
Sorry, I'm a bit late.

293
00:17:11,552 --> 00:17:14,722
Oh my, you both look absolutely radiant
this early in the morning.

294
00:17:14,805 --> 00:17:15,973
I look way too bare-faced.

295
00:17:16,057 --> 00:17:18,017
At your age, bare-faced is beautiful.

296
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,143
Go get changed.

297
00:17:26,317 --> 00:17:27,485
Hold on, what's with you?

298
00:17:27,568 --> 00:17:29,945
Already picking sides?
Without a word to me?

299
00:17:30,029 --> 00:17:31,155
Keep your friends close

300
00:17:31,238 --> 00:17:33,032
and your enemies closer.

301
00:17:33,115 --> 00:17:34,492
Don't you know that?

302
00:17:37,536 --> 00:17:39,121
We should grab a meal sometime.

303
00:17:39,205 --> 00:17:40,623
I'd love that.

304
00:17:45,628 --> 00:17:47,505
It's me. This just won't do.

305
00:17:47,588 --> 00:17:49,507
Dig up absolutely everything you can

306
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:51,676
on Cha Se-gye and send it right over.

307
00:17:53,928 --> 00:17:55,513
When did they get so close?

308
00:18:02,645 --> 00:18:03,562
Sir.

309
00:18:04,188 --> 00:18:06,524
You basically sealed the deal
with the date. What now?

310
00:18:06,607 --> 00:18:07,983
-Mr. Son.
-Sir.

311
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,860
I will handle my own private life,

312
00:18:09,944 --> 00:18:10,820
so butt out.

313
00:18:10,903 --> 00:18:12,655
I'm saying this because you aren't.

314
00:18:12,738 --> 00:18:14,073
Just look at this.

315
00:18:14,156 --> 00:18:15,991
The Mochang deal is front-page news.

316
00:18:16,075 --> 00:18:17,952
"Will they tie the knot next year?"

317
00:18:18,035 --> 00:18:21,080
"Is Biojei stock about to skyrocket?"
They're in a complete frenzy.

318
00:18:21,163 --> 00:18:22,248
We only met once.

319
00:18:22,331 --> 00:18:24,542
They're getting way ahead of themselves.

320
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:28,963
I have a way to fix all this,
so enough nagging.

321
00:18:33,926 --> 00:18:35,219
Mr. Son, by the way,

322
00:18:36,679 --> 00:18:39,098
does Shin Seo-ri look like
Ko Doo-shim to you?

323
00:18:39,932 --> 00:18:42,518
Why are you asking that all of a sudden?

324
00:18:43,894 --> 00:18:45,438
Here, try a bite of this.

325
00:18:46,105 --> 00:18:48,065
-Oh my.
-You ate that right up!

326
00:18:49,859 --> 00:18:52,486
-You eat with such relish.
-Is it good?

327
00:18:53,279 --> 00:18:54,155
Oh my.

328
00:18:54,238 --> 00:18:55,823
And such a pretty smile too.

329
00:18:55,906 --> 00:18:58,367
She's the spitting image
of a younger Doo-shim.

330
00:18:58,451 --> 00:18:59,618
Gosh, you're so right.

331
00:18:59,702 --> 00:19:01,829
-She really looks like Doo-shim.
-She does.

332
00:19:01,912 --> 00:19:04,290
-Oh my.
-Doo-shim? Is she your daughter?

333
00:19:04,373 --> 00:19:06,083
No, silly.

334
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:08,419
Ko Doo-shim. You don't know her?

335
00:19:08,502 --> 00:19:09,879
Ko Doo-shim?

336
00:19:10,629 --> 00:19:11,964
An actor beloved by the nation.

337
00:19:12,047 --> 00:19:14,341
The "Nation's Actor" is
your dream too, right?

338
00:19:14,425 --> 00:19:16,552
She's your competition. Your rival.

339
00:19:16,635 --> 00:19:17,970
My competition?

340
00:19:18,763 --> 00:19:19,764
Ko Doo-shim?

341
00:19:20,848 --> 00:19:22,558
-That's right.
-Want another one?

342
00:19:22,641 --> 00:19:24,602
Okay, coming right up.

343
00:19:24,685 --> 00:19:27,938
Gosh, you picked the biggest one.
Coming right up.

344
00:19:29,565 --> 00:19:31,525
Here you go.

345
00:19:41,577 --> 00:19:43,704
All right, here we go.

346
00:19:46,248 --> 00:19:48,375
Now, as the "Nation's Pebble,"

347
00:19:48,459 --> 00:19:51,796
you once rose to the top
of all the pebbles in the country.

348
00:19:51,879 --> 00:19:54,882
After such a long break,
I imagine your ambitions

349
00:19:54,965 --> 00:19:57,343
for this comeback must be immense.

350
00:19:57,426 --> 00:19:59,345
"Ride the wind. Break through the waves."

351
00:19:59,428 --> 00:20:01,472
I shall overcome any hardship

352
00:20:01,555 --> 00:20:03,682
and soar like a dragon meeting the clouds.

353
00:20:05,309 --> 00:20:07,686
Gosh, such impressive ambitions.

354
00:20:07,770 --> 00:20:09,563
Any other specific goals?

355
00:20:10,064 --> 00:20:11,941
My goal is Ko Doo-shim.

356
00:20:12,024 --> 00:20:14,360
Excuse me? The actor Ko Doo-shim?

357
00:20:14,443 --> 00:20:17,321
So, you want to become
an actor of her caliber?

358
00:20:17,404 --> 00:20:18,280
That's what you mean.

359
00:20:18,364 --> 00:20:19,490
-No.
-No?

360
00:20:19,573 --> 00:20:23,035
I shall sweep the top acting award
at all three major networks.

361
00:20:23,118 --> 00:20:24,453
Pardon?

362
00:20:24,537 --> 00:20:27,081
I reviewed the half-century history
of the entertainment industry

363
00:20:27,164 --> 00:20:29,792
and found that the only one
to ever sweep all three

364
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:31,085
was Ko Doo-shim.

365
00:20:31,168 --> 00:20:32,628
Like her, I shall sweep

366
00:20:32,711 --> 00:20:34,421
the acting awards, rise to prominence,

367
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:37,049
and become the finest performer
in this business.

368
00:20:38,676 --> 00:20:40,970
Good for you, Ko Doo-shim.

369
00:20:41,262 --> 00:20:42,179
SHIN SEO-RI, PROFILE

370
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:44,890
Is anyone doing their job over there?

371
00:20:44,974 --> 00:20:46,517
Excuse me? What…

372
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:50,312
Shin Seo-ri's profile on the portal site
hasn't even been updated properly.

373
00:20:51,063 --> 00:20:53,440
How lazy is her agency?

374
00:20:53,983 --> 00:20:55,359
We are her agency, sir.

375
00:20:55,442 --> 00:20:56,402
Exactly.

376
00:20:56,485 --> 00:20:59,738
Tell them to send the best shots
as soon as they come in.

377
00:20:59,822 --> 00:21:03,075
And don't forget to get my final approval
before sending them out.

378
00:21:03,534 --> 00:21:04,869
Yes, sir.

379
00:21:07,329 --> 00:21:09,206
And this is also very important.

380
00:21:09,915 --> 00:21:11,417
She has no bad side. No bad angles.

381
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:12,835
So I want a range of angles.

382
00:21:12,918 --> 00:21:15,254
She's pretty without retouching,
so make sure to send me

383
00:21:15,337 --> 00:21:16,881
the originals.

384
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,717
You aren't even hiding it now.

385
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:20,926
Sir, do you really--

386
00:21:21,010 --> 00:21:22,386
Yes, that's right.

387
00:21:22,469 --> 00:21:24,096
We've got a thing going on.

388
00:21:24,763 --> 00:21:26,432
Is this "thing" mutual?

389
00:21:26,515 --> 00:21:27,933
Obviously.

390
00:21:28,017 --> 00:21:31,812
As if I'd be pathetic enough to have
a one-sided crush at my age.

391
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:34,982
There's a chance.

392
00:21:37,109 --> 00:21:38,360
SHIN SEO-RI

393
00:21:38,444 --> 00:21:40,696
Still, how does this make any sense?

394
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,243
Excuse me.

395
00:21:46,327 --> 00:21:48,037
How can you park illegally
for over an hour

396
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,789
in front of someone else's building,
like you own the place?

397
00:21:50,873 --> 00:21:52,249
If you block traffic like this,

398
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,752
your car could get towed.

399
00:21:54,835 --> 00:21:56,003
Are you the landlord?

400
00:21:56,086 --> 00:21:57,546
Landlord…

401
00:21:57,630 --> 00:21:59,590
No, I'm not the landlord.

402
00:21:59,673 --> 00:22:01,550
I am in charge
of keeping watch over this building.

403
00:22:01,634 --> 00:22:02,885
So you're the manager.

404
00:22:02,968 --> 00:22:05,471
Is the rooftop here being leased or owned?

405
00:22:05,554 --> 00:22:07,348
It's leased, but why do you ask?

406
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:11,226
So there's no big money
changing hands between them yet.

407
00:22:12,811 --> 00:22:13,812
Keep up the work.

408
00:22:13,896 --> 00:22:16,231
Pardon? What's with this lady?

409
00:22:16,315 --> 00:22:18,901
It appears the chairman is very serious

410
00:22:18,984 --> 00:22:20,986
about this marital alliance with Mochang.

411
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:23,447
That utterly unflappable man cemented it
with a press release.

412
00:22:23,530 --> 00:22:25,908
He must have been beyond thrilled.

413
00:22:32,623 --> 00:22:34,083
Sir, I have an important update.

414
00:22:34,166 --> 00:22:35,459
Go ahead.

415
00:22:36,710 --> 00:22:37,753
Mr. Cha Se-gye's team

416
00:22:37,836 --> 00:22:40,589
requested police protection for the nurse.

417
00:22:40,673 --> 00:22:42,549
She hasn't regained consciousness yet--

418
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:44,843
Meaning she could wake up anytime.

419
00:22:44,927 --> 00:22:48,013
And that the job wasn't handled perfectly.

420
00:22:54,937 --> 00:22:57,690
The frontal lobe damage from her fall

421
00:22:57,773 --> 00:22:59,858
led to a subarachnoid hemorrhage.

422
00:23:06,323 --> 00:23:07,199
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

423
00:23:07,282 --> 00:23:09,243
How did something like this
happen in my clinic…

424
00:23:09,326 --> 00:23:10,202
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

425
00:23:10,285 --> 00:23:12,037
Nothing is certain yet.

426
00:23:12,579 --> 00:23:14,957
We'll investigate properly
when she wakes up.

427
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,001
Let's pause your meds for now.

428
00:23:17,084 --> 00:23:19,253
You should stay vigilant
and be careful too.

429
00:23:19,878 --> 00:23:20,963
Don't worry.

430
00:23:21,505 --> 00:23:23,507
I can protect myself just fine.

431
00:23:29,013 --> 00:23:31,015
Gosh. Goodness me.

432
00:23:38,731 --> 00:23:40,983
Earning a living is no joke.

433
00:23:41,066 --> 00:23:43,027
Feels like I got beaten to a pulp.

434
00:23:43,610 --> 00:23:45,904
The world beyond your doorstep is brutal.

435
00:23:45,988 --> 00:23:47,156
Nothing in life is easy.

436
00:23:47,239 --> 00:23:49,241
You sure make it look easy.

437
00:23:49,324 --> 00:23:51,952
Just tagging along, doing nothing,
and getting paid for it.

438
00:23:52,036 --> 00:23:52,953
Must be nice.

439
00:23:53,037 --> 00:23:55,456
So that's the mindset
of those crooked employers

440
00:23:55,539 --> 00:23:57,416
who cheat people out of their wages.

441
00:23:59,501 --> 00:24:00,711
Oh right.

442
00:24:01,336 --> 00:24:02,463
Here.

443
00:24:03,005 --> 00:24:05,549
The resort gave this to me.
Said it was yours.

444
00:24:05,632 --> 00:24:08,177
They said you'd understand
if I said "licorice taffy."

445
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:09,428
I'll be going now.

446
00:24:09,928 --> 00:24:12,056
-My back.
-Jeez.

447
00:24:21,732 --> 00:24:24,443
<i>Thank you. Wishing you sweet happiness.</i>

448
00:24:25,152 --> 00:24:26,779
Sweet, my foot.

449
00:24:47,216 --> 00:24:48,550
<i>You said you liked the sea.</i>

450
00:24:48,634 --> 00:24:50,594
Just sober up a bit before we go.

451
00:24:52,638 --> 00:24:53,514
Very well, then.

452
00:25:13,325 --> 00:25:15,327
Being all sweet, so unlike him.

453
00:25:16,578 --> 00:25:18,455
You grabbed me first.

454
00:25:20,415 --> 00:25:22,584
And what was with that smoldering look?

455
00:25:23,544 --> 00:25:24,920
Damn sinner.

456
00:25:25,629 --> 00:25:28,549
<i>I see you bear</i>
<i>the face of a sinner as well.</i>

457
00:25:28,632 --> 00:25:30,884
You will surely end up breaking
many a maiden's heart.

458
00:25:30,968 --> 00:25:32,928
That face is destined for high treason.

459
00:25:48,152 --> 00:25:49,528
<i>I must be insane.</i>

460
00:25:57,995 --> 00:26:00,455
Be honest. You were never
"romantically impotent," were you?

461
00:26:00,539 --> 00:26:02,082
You're a pro, right? Busted.

462
00:26:03,125 --> 00:26:05,544
You toyed with me like I was some yo-yo.

463
00:26:06,712 --> 00:26:07,796
What the…

464
00:26:14,928 --> 00:26:17,890
Meanwhile, my heart feels like
it's about to burst.

465
00:26:29,151 --> 00:26:30,986
I really need to quit drinking.

466
00:26:31,069 --> 00:26:33,739
I almost made a huge mistake.

467
00:26:33,822 --> 00:26:34,823
Yikes.

468
00:26:42,247 --> 00:26:43,207
<i>How romantic.</i>

469
00:26:43,290 --> 00:26:44,833
Our very own Mont Saint-Michel.

470
00:26:44,917 --> 00:26:46,251
So are we official now?

471
00:26:48,378 --> 00:26:50,464
He is a bottomless pit of drunk nonsense.

472
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:56,178
But what was he even talking about?

473
00:26:57,179 --> 00:26:58,722
"Monsoon Seashell"?

474
00:27:00,015 --> 00:27:01,266
"Monsoon Seashore"?

475
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:03,352
Mont Saint-Michel?

476
00:27:32,798 --> 00:27:34,716
No wonder you make hearts ache.

477
00:27:47,104 --> 00:27:48,188
<i>I do not.</i>

478
00:27:48,272 --> 00:27:49,314
I have no memory of that.

479
00:27:49,398 --> 00:27:50,440
Wait, you blacked out?

480
00:27:52,859 --> 00:27:55,404
She smashes my heart to pieces,

481
00:27:57,155 --> 00:27:59,116
and she's the one who blacks out?

482
00:28:02,452 --> 00:28:04,538
What a selfish woman.

483
00:28:05,956 --> 00:28:07,416
Is she sleeping?

484
00:28:12,754 --> 00:28:15,382
ARE YOU SLEEPING?

485
00:28:17,884 --> 00:28:20,512
SHIN SEO-RI

486
00:28:21,638 --> 00:28:22,889
No.

487
00:28:25,976 --> 00:28:27,227
It's not cool

488
00:28:27,936 --> 00:28:29,938
for a man to be clingy.

489
00:28:46,997 --> 00:28:49,916
Se-gye, how was your business trip?

490
00:28:50,834 --> 00:28:51,710
Who is this?

491
00:28:51,793 --> 00:28:52,961
This is Mo Tae-hee.

492
00:28:53,045 --> 00:28:55,797
<i>I guess you haven't saved my number yet.</i>

493
00:28:55,881 --> 00:28:58,342
I only save the numbers of people
I've met at least twice.

494
00:28:58,425 --> 00:29:00,510
Then you can save it now.

495
00:29:00,594 --> 00:29:02,554
I'll be near your place soon.

496
00:29:02,637 --> 00:29:04,097
Should we meet up?

497
00:29:05,390 --> 00:29:06,850
We also have things to discuss

498
00:29:06,933 --> 00:29:08,143
<i>regarding the Mochang deal.</i>

499
00:29:08,226 --> 00:29:10,270
You even know my address
despite me never telling you.

500
00:29:10,354 --> 00:29:11,855
<i>You gather intel pretty fast.</i>

501
00:29:11,938 --> 00:29:14,399
You can discuss
the deal directly with Grandfather.

502
00:29:14,483 --> 00:29:17,069
Officially, I'm an outsider
when it comes to Chail.

503
00:29:17,152 --> 00:29:18,779
Are you upset again?

504
00:29:18,862 --> 00:29:21,531
There's no reason to be upset.
It's still a green light for business.

505
00:29:21,615 --> 00:29:24,117
However, we need to clear up
a few things personally.

506
00:29:24,201 --> 00:29:25,660
You should delete my number.

507
00:29:25,744 --> 00:29:27,537
<i>A company like Mochang has plenty</i>

508
00:29:27,621 --> 00:29:29,456
of good options besides Chail.

509
00:29:30,248 --> 00:29:31,875
Let's conclude our arrangement here.

510
00:29:31,958 --> 00:29:34,086
Well, sure, if that's what you want.

511
00:29:34,169 --> 00:29:35,879
<i>Sorry for calling so late.</i>

512
00:29:42,844 --> 00:29:44,429
That takes care of that.

513
00:29:45,389 --> 00:29:47,891
I can't give Shin Seo-ri
anything to hold over me.

514
00:29:48,642 --> 00:29:51,103
Do you live here alone, young lady?

515
00:29:51,186 --> 00:29:52,229
No family living with you?

516
00:29:52,312 --> 00:29:55,315
Must I answer every question
from an uninvited guest?

517
00:29:55,399 --> 00:29:57,359
I'm his aunt.

518
00:29:57,442 --> 00:29:59,194
I'll get straight to the point.

519
00:29:59,277 --> 00:30:00,904
What's your relationship with Se-gye?

520
00:30:00,987 --> 00:30:03,031
Why would you come here to ask that?

521
00:30:03,115 --> 00:30:05,450
If you are his aunt,
you ought to ask him directly.

522
00:30:05,534 --> 00:30:07,160
Seeing as you made this journey,

523
00:30:07,244 --> 00:30:09,913
you and your nephew
must be quite estranged.

524
00:30:11,748 --> 00:30:14,376
Judging by the way you fire back,

525
00:30:14,459 --> 00:30:15,961
you're no pushover.

526
00:30:16,044 --> 00:30:19,798
You must've had quite a few men
fawning at your feet.

527
00:30:19,881 --> 00:30:21,299
That's my expertise.

528
00:30:21,383 --> 00:30:23,051
I've got you figured out now.

529
00:30:26,638 --> 00:30:27,764
<i>Could this be</i>

530
00:30:27,848 --> 00:30:30,892
<i>what those chaebol mothers-in-law use</i>
<i>to tear couples apart?</i>

531
00:30:30,976 --> 00:30:32,811
<i>The infamous envelope</i>

532
00:30:32,894 --> 00:30:34,771
<i>that appears every time without fail?</i>

533
00:30:37,274 --> 00:30:39,317
What a familiar sight.

534
00:30:40,402 --> 00:30:42,070
Usually, mothers-in-law bring these out.

535
00:30:42,154 --> 00:30:44,823
But it seems aunts
are quite fond of them too.

536
00:30:44,906 --> 00:30:47,284
It sounds like this isn't your first one.

537
00:30:47,826 --> 00:30:49,244
Are you a pro in these parts?

538
00:30:49,327 --> 00:30:50,245
Then I suppose

539
00:30:50,328 --> 00:30:52,456
I can skip the lengthy explanation.

540
00:30:53,248 --> 00:30:55,417
-Se-gye--
-I cannot part ways with Cha Se-gye.

541
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:56,376
You can't?

542
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:58,712
I am sorry, but I cannot.

543
00:30:58,795 --> 00:30:59,921
Well, there is a contract,

544
00:31:00,005 --> 00:31:02,466
and our relationship is not one
that can easily end.

545
00:31:03,049 --> 00:31:04,593
So you two are serious enough

546
00:31:04,676 --> 00:31:06,386
that one envelope won't cut it?

547
00:31:06,470 --> 00:31:10,098
No. This matter is
beyond how serious we are.

548
00:31:10,849 --> 00:31:13,685
Then that's even better.

549
00:31:13,768 --> 00:31:15,770
If things are already that complicated,

550
00:31:15,854 --> 00:31:18,273
take this and just tie him down for good.

551
00:31:18,356 --> 00:31:20,025
If you found yourself knocked up too,

552
00:31:20,108 --> 00:31:21,318
that'd be <i>mucho gracias.</i>

553
00:31:22,277 --> 00:31:24,779
So you are not asking me

554
00:31:24,863 --> 00:31:26,448
to take this and begone?

555
00:31:26,531 --> 00:31:28,783
Leave? Of course not.

556
00:31:28,867 --> 00:31:30,410
I'm asking you to stick by

557
00:31:30,494 --> 00:31:33,788
that punk Se-gye like super taffy.

558
00:31:33,872 --> 00:31:34,789
What?

559
00:31:35,499 --> 00:31:36,958
"Super taffy"?

560
00:31:37,042 --> 00:31:37,959
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

561
00:31:38,043 --> 00:31:39,127
What the…

562
00:31:39,211 --> 00:31:40,629
NO PARKING

563
00:31:40,712 --> 00:31:42,130
This lady is unbelievable.

564
00:31:42,214 --> 00:31:44,466
I even asked her so nicely.

565
00:31:44,549 --> 00:31:46,593
Does she take me for some chump?

566
00:31:47,552 --> 00:31:49,304
Given your situation,

567
00:31:49,387 --> 00:31:52,432
you were likely snooping around
for money and got lucky.

568
00:31:52,516 --> 00:31:55,435
I welcome your relationship
with open arms.

569
00:31:55,519 --> 00:31:58,396
Thus, to force us even closer together,

570
00:31:59,147 --> 00:32:00,774
you brought this envelope.

571
00:32:00,857 --> 00:32:02,067
Even better if it lasts

572
00:32:02,150 --> 00:32:03,985
until the end of the Mochang partnership.

573
00:32:04,069 --> 00:32:07,572
Or if you just stay by his side forever,

574
00:32:07,656 --> 00:32:09,991
that'd be the icing
on the most beautiful cake.

575
00:32:11,117 --> 00:32:14,204
You all treat me
like some plague-ridden leper.

576
00:32:14,287 --> 00:32:15,830
So you stood up. Now what?

577
00:32:15,914 --> 00:32:17,916
Did that measly pride of yours
take a blow?

578
00:32:17,999 --> 00:32:21,086
How dare you glare at an elder like that!

579
00:32:21,169 --> 00:32:24,339
Then you should have comported yourself
with the dignity of one!

580
00:32:28,510 --> 00:32:30,220
Hey, this is straight-up assault!

581
00:32:30,303 --> 00:32:32,681
Not assault.
Just giving you your beloved super taffy.

582
00:32:32,764 --> 00:32:33,974
-That hurts!
-Damn it.

583
00:32:34,057 --> 00:32:35,850
That hurts! Stop it already!

584
00:32:40,438 --> 00:32:43,191
She's crazy! A total lunatic!
An absolute psycho!

585
00:32:43,275 --> 00:32:45,151
Where did such an uncultured…

586
00:32:45,235 --> 00:32:47,862
What the hell was she throwing?
I'm aching all over.

587
00:32:47,946 --> 00:32:49,739
Wait, where's my car?

588
00:32:52,492 --> 00:32:53,743
What's that?

589
00:32:56,913 --> 00:33:00,292
"Subject to fine and towing."

590
00:33:00,375 --> 00:33:01,876
Who did this?

591
00:33:05,922 --> 00:33:07,841
I warned you, didn't I?

592
00:33:07,924 --> 00:33:09,593
Park illegally and you get towed.

593
00:33:16,558 --> 00:33:19,102
They are all trying
to make me their scapegoat.

594
00:33:19,185 --> 00:33:21,187
As if I were the plague itself.

595
00:33:46,004 --> 00:33:47,631
Beautiful.

596
00:33:48,381 --> 00:33:49,341
That's a keeper.

597
00:33:49,424 --> 00:33:53,762
FAVORITES

598
00:33:57,891 --> 00:34:00,727
Her beauty is
really something else. Seriously.

599
00:34:06,107 --> 00:34:08,943
Sir, you seem to be
in another good mood today.

600
00:34:09,778 --> 00:34:10,987
Is it obvious?

601
00:34:12,614 --> 00:34:14,699
How am I supposed to pick just one?

602
00:34:14,783 --> 00:34:17,827
You must be deciding on a gift.

603
00:34:18,328 --> 00:34:20,705
-A gift?
-For Ms. Shin's birthday.

604
00:34:22,165 --> 00:34:23,750
It's her birthday?

605
00:34:25,877 --> 00:34:27,170
That thing has more than photos.

606
00:34:27,253 --> 00:34:28,463
It also tells you the date.

607
00:34:28,546 --> 00:34:30,632
This is your chance to score some points.

608
00:34:32,676 --> 00:34:35,053
Why are you cheering me on, Mr. Son?

609
00:34:35,136 --> 00:34:37,722
Are you ditching Grandfather
to join my side?

610
00:34:39,015 --> 00:34:40,975
What can I say? Time flies,

611
00:34:41,059 --> 00:34:43,103
and you have a bright future ahead.

612
00:34:43,687 --> 00:34:44,979
Going all in on my future asset.

613
00:34:45,063 --> 00:34:45,939
Good thinking.

614
00:34:46,022 --> 00:34:48,608
Then I'll entrust you
with our most urgent task.

615
00:34:48,692 --> 00:34:50,652
Theme park, drone show,
10,000 flowers. Get it done.

616
00:34:50,735 --> 00:34:51,861
-That won't do.
-Why not?

617
00:34:51,945 --> 00:34:52,821
It's too cliché.

618
00:34:52,904 --> 00:34:54,614
The same old repertoire is too boring.

619
00:34:54,698 --> 00:34:57,158
Aren't classics guaranteed to be hits?

620
00:34:57,242 --> 00:34:59,536
Not at all. It's just a waste of money.

621
00:35:01,204 --> 00:35:02,831
At least you're theoretically flawless.

622
00:35:02,914 --> 00:35:04,874
Then why do you live alone with a cat?

623
00:35:04,958 --> 00:35:06,668
I'm single by choice.

624
00:35:08,002 --> 00:35:08,920
Yeah, right.

625
00:35:18,972 --> 00:35:19,973
Hey.

626
00:35:20,557 --> 00:35:21,641
Is your birthday coming up?

627
00:35:22,475 --> 00:35:23,351
My birthday?

628
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:27,355
If there's anything you want, let me know.

629
00:35:27,439 --> 00:35:29,482
Just make sure it's under 30,000 won.

630
00:35:29,566 --> 00:35:30,734
I have no use for gifts.

631
00:35:30,817 --> 00:35:32,444
Suit yourself. Works for me.

632
00:35:33,027 --> 00:35:34,738
Take this. Come down when you're ready.

633
00:35:34,821 --> 00:35:36,072
I'll be downstairs.

634
00:35:38,533 --> 00:35:41,244
WISHING YOU A HAPPY BIRTHDAY
MS. SHIN SEO-RI

635
00:35:48,918 --> 00:35:50,712
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, VALUED CUSTOMER

636
00:35:57,927 --> 00:35:59,012
Just forget it.

637
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:01,806
It is not even yours anyway.

638
00:36:08,146 --> 00:36:09,230
<i>He's my man.</i>

639
00:36:12,942 --> 00:36:14,068
Se-gye and I

640
00:36:14,152 --> 00:36:15,945
are going to be married.

641
00:36:16,029 --> 00:36:18,239
I'm not telling you to break up now.

642
00:36:18,323 --> 00:36:21,743
I was planning to tolerate
a woman or two on the side,

643
00:36:21,826 --> 00:36:24,037
even after we got married anyway.

644
00:36:24,621 --> 00:36:27,248
In that sense, someone like you would be

645
00:36:27,332 --> 00:36:28,291
pretty convenient.

646
00:36:28,917 --> 00:36:31,711
I know not what rumors you have heard…

647
00:36:33,463 --> 00:36:35,924
but I have not
the slightest intention of becoming

648
00:36:36,424 --> 00:36:37,634
such a plaything.

649
00:36:37,717 --> 00:36:39,302
If you wish to leave in one piece,

650
00:36:39,385 --> 00:36:41,971
I suggest you keep that trap shut.

651
00:36:45,975 --> 00:36:47,477
You're much more blunt

652
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:49,395
than what I gathered
from your background check.

653
00:36:49,479 --> 00:36:51,731
This is why you can't trust
anything on paper.

654
00:36:54,609 --> 00:36:56,319
Better get used
to that level of humiliation.

655
00:36:56,402 --> 00:36:58,613
Because that's exactly your position.

656
00:36:59,155 --> 00:37:00,532
-What was that?
-I plan

657
00:37:00,615 --> 00:37:03,493
to place a crown on Se-gye's head.

658
00:37:03,576 --> 00:37:05,870
I have that kind of power.

659
00:37:05,954 --> 00:37:07,831
But you…

660
00:37:12,502 --> 00:37:13,795
<i>What exactly</i>

661
00:37:13,878 --> 00:37:17,006
can you do for him?

662
00:37:31,688 --> 00:37:32,897
Did you hear?

663
00:37:32,981 --> 00:37:36,109
A marriage proposal was delivered
to Seonghyeon Pavilion this morning.

664
00:37:36,192 --> 00:37:38,361
I guess the prince is getting married.

665
00:37:38,444 --> 00:37:40,488
But to whom?
Who would marry the Ghost Prince?

666
00:37:40,572 --> 00:37:41,948
A nine-tailed fox?

667
00:37:42,699 --> 00:37:43,700
Wait.

668
00:37:44,784 --> 00:37:46,202
Is that true?

669
00:37:47,412 --> 00:37:49,539
<i>I guess once His Highness</i>
<i>leaves the palace,</i>

670
00:37:49,622 --> 00:37:51,332
<i>you will have nowhere to go.</i>

671
00:37:51,416 --> 00:37:54,043
<i>That is why being a court lady</i>
<i>is such a sorry fate.</i>

672
00:37:54,127 --> 00:37:57,338
<i>Our lives solely depend on</i>
<i>the masters we serve.</i>

673
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:03,511
<i>Why do all this</i>

674
00:38:03,595 --> 00:38:05,388
<i>if you were just going to leave?</i>

675
00:38:06,014 --> 00:38:07,974
It is a <i>Cheomjado</i> from Qing.

676
00:38:08,057 --> 00:38:10,435
A gift for my dearest companion.

677
00:38:10,518 --> 00:38:11,728
<i>But now we have trouble afoot.</i>

678
00:38:11,811 --> 00:38:13,730
<i>You have already come too close,</i>

679
00:38:13,813 --> 00:38:15,982
<i>and you even know all about my secret.</i>

680
00:38:16,065 --> 00:38:17,609
<i>What shall I do with you now?</i>

681
00:38:17,692 --> 00:38:18,818
<i>You should never have shown</i>

682
00:38:18,902 --> 00:38:20,320
such kindness to a mere court lady.

683
00:38:55,647 --> 00:38:58,149
<i>I must sever any affection</i>
<i>before it takes root.</i>

684
00:38:58,775 --> 00:39:00,985
<i>Eradicate it as if it had never existed.</i>

685
00:39:01,611 --> 00:39:02,946
<i>After sincerity departs,</i>

686
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:06,074
<i>only bitter traces will remain.</i>

687
00:39:22,382 --> 00:39:25,843
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM
SEASON 2, EPISODE 6

688
00:39:25,927 --> 00:39:26,803
Your Majesty,

689
00:39:26,886 --> 00:39:28,805
what is the meaning of this?

690
00:39:28,888 --> 00:39:29,764
You wench!

691
00:39:29,847 --> 00:39:31,933
I fed and housed you
when you had nowhere to go,

692
00:39:32,016 --> 00:39:33,393
and you dare betray me?

693
00:39:33,476 --> 00:39:34,852
I have served His Majesty.

694
00:39:34,936 --> 00:39:36,604
-You must preserve decorum.
-Hear me!

695
00:39:36,688 --> 00:39:39,148
Do not just stand idly by.
Drag this wench away at once!

696
00:39:39,232 --> 00:39:42,527
-Yes, Your Majesty.
-Announcing His Majesty!

697
00:39:46,447 --> 00:39:48,658
What is this commotion?

698
00:39:50,952 --> 00:39:52,161
A woman's screaming

699
00:39:52,245 --> 00:39:54,539
can be heard from the forecourt
of my royal chambers.

700
00:39:54,622 --> 00:39:56,040
Even if it is an Inner Court matter,

701
00:39:56,124 --> 00:39:57,542
I could no longer stand idly by.

702
00:39:57,625 --> 00:39:59,961
Your Majesty, my foolish ignorance

703
00:40:00,044 --> 00:40:02,338
led me to greatly offend Her Majesty.

704
00:40:02,964 --> 00:40:04,382
I deserve death.

705
00:40:07,343 --> 00:40:08,219
Your Majesty.

706
00:40:08,302 --> 00:40:10,763
This is strictly
a matter of the Inner Court.

707
00:40:10,847 --> 00:40:14,517
I am merely fulfilling my duty,
so I beseech you for your understanding.

708
00:40:16,769 --> 00:40:18,646
What in the world?

709
00:40:18,730 --> 00:40:19,939
Look here.

710
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:22,233
Hear me.

711
00:40:22,316 --> 00:40:23,359
Fetch the Royal Physician!

712
00:40:23,443 --> 00:40:24,986
Court Lady Park, move Court Lady Kim

713
00:40:25,069 --> 00:40:26,696
into the Queen's Quarters at once!

714
00:40:26,779 --> 00:40:28,364
Yes, Your Majesty.

715
00:40:28,448 --> 00:40:29,699
How dare you!

716
00:40:29,782 --> 00:40:31,034
That will not do.

717
00:40:32,118 --> 00:40:33,578
Let us go to the annex.

718
00:40:38,708 --> 00:40:40,001
Let us go.

719
00:40:44,297 --> 00:40:46,174
Cut! That was great. Excellent!

720
00:40:46,257 --> 00:40:47,550
-Oh, my back.
-Seriously.

721
00:40:47,633 --> 00:40:49,635
Wasn't that improv amazing?
B Cam, you got it?

722
00:40:49,719 --> 00:40:51,554
She's even great at improv too.

723
00:40:51,637 --> 00:40:52,638
Where'd you learn that?

724
00:40:52,722 --> 00:40:54,932
All right, let's move on
to the next scene.

725
00:40:56,100 --> 00:40:58,144
Director, how could you?

726
00:40:58,227 --> 00:41:00,688
You hated Shin Seo-ri
for being a favor hire.

727
00:41:00,772 --> 00:41:03,191
What can I do
when she acts up a storm like that?

728
00:41:03,274 --> 00:41:05,109
I mean, when I was watching
the edit yesterday,

729
00:41:05,193 --> 00:41:07,904
I really thought she time-slipped
straight out of Joseon for a second.

730
00:41:07,987 --> 00:41:09,322
Even so,

731
00:41:09,405 --> 00:41:12,033
the nameless Court Lady Kim became
a Favored Court Lady in two episodes.

732
00:41:12,116 --> 00:41:13,576
How does that make any sense?

733
00:41:13,659 --> 00:41:15,828
She was basically a lead
in today's climax scene.

734
00:41:15,912 --> 00:41:16,788
Ji-hyo.

735
00:41:17,413 --> 00:41:20,166
As a drama goes on for more seasons,

736
00:41:20,249 --> 00:41:22,460
a new villain must appear to keep it fun.

737
00:41:22,543 --> 00:41:24,128
That's what will make it a hit.

738
00:41:24,212 --> 00:41:26,130
You know this. Don't be an amateur.

739
00:41:26,756 --> 00:41:28,341
Am I wrong? Are you upset?

740
00:41:29,008 --> 00:41:30,968
Well, not exactly, but--

741
00:41:31,052 --> 00:41:33,262
Just be patient.
I'll put in a good word with the writer.

742
00:41:33,346 --> 00:41:35,181
You'll be fine. You're doing great.

743
00:41:35,264 --> 00:41:37,183
Have some more confidence in yourself.

744
00:41:39,185 --> 00:41:41,229
Just because she snagged herself
a man with a supercar,

745
00:41:41,312 --> 00:41:42,772
she's suddenly too good for everyone.

746
00:41:42,855 --> 00:41:43,940
What was it? Gwang-sam?

747
00:41:44,023 --> 00:41:44,941
Gwang-pal?

748
00:41:45,858 --> 00:41:47,276
Hey!

749
00:41:47,777 --> 00:41:49,237
I'm going all out today.

750
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:51,239
I need to go absolutely full glam today.

751
00:41:51,322 --> 00:41:53,533
Han Min-hui might be there. Damn it.

752
00:41:54,033 --> 00:41:55,535
-Give it.
-Sure.

753
00:42:03,668 --> 00:42:04,919
<i>You're all dead.</i>

754
00:42:15,429 --> 00:42:16,347
Perfect.

755
00:42:20,935 --> 00:42:21,811
JI-HYO, I'M HERE AGAIN

756
00:42:21,894 --> 00:42:23,521
-Over here!
-Ji-hyo!

757
00:42:23,604 --> 00:42:24,897
Please look over here.

758
00:42:29,193 --> 00:42:31,529
<i>What a beautiful night.</i>

759
00:42:36,659 --> 00:42:40,121
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

760
00:42:48,379 --> 00:42:51,883
There should at least be
some sort of lock on the entrance.

761
00:43:16,157 --> 00:43:18,868
The landlord should've installed
window guards.

762
00:43:23,122 --> 00:43:25,958
A woman lives here alone,
and it couldn't be darker.

763
00:43:27,793 --> 00:43:29,712
<i>Let's pause your meds for now.</i>

764
00:43:29,795 --> 00:43:31,964
<i>You should stay vigilant</i>
<i>and be careful too.</i>

765
00:43:32,924 --> 00:43:35,426
If anything, she needs
to be more vigilant than me.

766
00:43:44,977 --> 00:43:46,479
I told her to toss them.

767
00:43:47,230 --> 00:43:48,731
At least she brought it home.

768
00:43:50,399 --> 00:43:52,068
What are you doing here?

769
00:44:04,205 --> 00:44:05,748
Let's just move you out of here.

770
00:44:05,831 --> 00:44:08,125
No window guards, zero security.

771
00:44:08,209 --> 00:44:09,377
It makes me too anxious.

772
00:44:09,460 --> 00:44:11,003
I am fond of this place.

773
00:44:11,087 --> 00:44:12,964
Cease your fussing and begone.

774
00:44:13,464 --> 00:44:14,799
You're an actor too.

775
00:44:14,882 --> 00:44:17,301
Not just an extra.
You're a real celebrity now.

776
00:44:17,385 --> 00:44:20,346
Do you think you can live
a normal life, out in the open like this?

777
00:44:20,429 --> 00:44:22,181
Its openness is what I like about it.

778
00:44:22,265 --> 00:44:24,809
It is hard to breathe
in cramped and dark spaces.

779
00:44:28,187 --> 00:44:29,355
All right.

780
00:44:29,438 --> 00:44:32,233
I'll tell the agency
to get you a bigger place.

781
00:44:32,316 --> 00:44:33,526
Start packing now.

782
00:44:33,609 --> 00:44:35,194
Stop making me worry about you.

783
00:44:35,695 --> 00:44:37,488
Who asked you to worry about me?

784
00:44:37,571 --> 00:44:39,824
Whether I live somewhere wide open
or miserably cramped,

785
00:44:39,907 --> 00:44:41,367
pay me no mind.

786
00:44:41,909 --> 00:44:43,786
Why are you being so difficult today?

787
00:44:43,869 --> 00:44:45,329
Did things go wrong on set?

788
00:44:45,413 --> 00:44:46,956
Did someone give you a hard time?

789
00:44:47,039 --> 00:44:48,207
Tell me everything. I'll fix--

790
00:44:48,291 --> 00:44:50,793
Stop. Just stop doing anything for me.

791
00:44:54,338 --> 00:44:55,631
I no longer wish…

792
00:44:56,757 --> 00:44:58,634
to use you as my shield.

793
00:44:58,718 --> 00:45:00,428
I do not want your concern either.

794
00:45:00,928 --> 00:45:03,556
In this place, protecting myself
is overwhelming enough.

795
00:45:03,639 --> 00:45:05,599
I want to live without these burdens.

796
00:45:05,683 --> 00:45:07,893
The thought of someone
holding me in their heart

797
00:45:07,977 --> 00:45:09,770
is too heavy a burden to bear.

798
00:45:11,022 --> 00:45:12,398
So cease this now.

799
00:45:15,526 --> 00:45:16,861
Since there is…

800
00:45:18,863 --> 00:45:20,740
nothing I can do for you either.

801
00:45:46,140 --> 00:45:47,641
Then what's this?

802
00:45:53,022 --> 00:45:55,983
Why bring this back if you hate the idea
of taking space in someone's heart?

803
00:45:56,067 --> 00:45:57,818
That is merely a token of memory…

804
00:46:01,697 --> 00:46:02,698
<i>To ensure good memories</i>

805
00:46:02,782 --> 00:46:04,867
are not easily forgotten,

806
00:46:05,785 --> 00:46:07,995
one must collect tokens like this.

807
00:46:12,333 --> 00:46:14,043
You remember everything.

808
00:46:15,336 --> 00:46:17,171
So you were just acting?

809
00:46:19,006 --> 00:46:21,008
Pretending like you didn't remember.

810
00:46:21,092 --> 00:46:22,510
Like nothing happened.

811
00:46:22,593 --> 00:46:23,928
Yes, I was.

812
00:46:25,137 --> 00:46:28,349
I feigned it because I did not wish
to be further entangled with you.

813
00:46:29,225 --> 00:46:30,726
You're not even denying it.

814
00:46:33,020 --> 00:46:34,397
Do you really…

815
00:46:44,448 --> 00:46:47,118
-Am I never going to be the one for you?
-No.

816
00:46:47,618 --> 00:46:48,744
You never will be.

817
00:46:48,828 --> 00:46:51,038
I am enough for myself in this world.

818
00:46:51,122 --> 00:46:53,082
And even if I were to need a man,

819
00:46:53,165 --> 00:46:54,583
it will never be you.

820
00:46:58,087 --> 00:46:58,963
"Never"?

821
00:46:59,046 --> 00:47:00,923
Do not come here unannounced anymore.

822
00:47:02,007 --> 00:47:03,717
It is tiresome to deal with you.

823
00:47:17,314 --> 00:47:18,774
It will never be you.

824
00:47:22,069 --> 00:47:23,612
That stings.

825
00:47:26,449 --> 00:47:27,867
Shin Seo-ri.

826
00:47:35,958 --> 00:47:37,835
<i>If you let no one in,</i>

827
00:47:37,918 --> 00:47:39,670
<i>you will never be broken.</i>

828
00:47:40,629 --> 00:47:42,339
<i>If you remain perfectly still,</i>

829
00:47:42,423 --> 00:47:44,258
<i>nothing will ever happen to you.</i>

830
00:47:47,928 --> 00:47:50,347
There's no getting through
to the Mochang side.

831
00:47:50,431 --> 00:47:51,557
Any updates?

832
00:47:51,640 --> 00:47:54,643
Resort security says they suspect
Mr. Cha drove drunk,

833
00:47:54,727 --> 00:47:56,520
but a video taken by a staff member

834
00:47:56,604 --> 00:47:58,105
confirms he did not drink.

835
00:48:05,529 --> 00:48:07,198
That's not bad.

836
00:48:07,281 --> 00:48:08,991
Let's go with this.

837
00:48:09,074 --> 00:48:12,036
Sir? They said he wasn't actually…

838
00:48:12,119 --> 00:48:13,996
Does the truth matter?

839
00:48:14,079 --> 00:48:15,581
You saw what happened
with the deepfake.

840
00:48:15,664 --> 00:48:18,792
People don't care about retractions.

841
00:48:18,876 --> 00:48:19,793
At this point,

842
00:48:19,877 --> 00:48:22,129
we need to take decisive action.

843
00:48:22,213 --> 00:48:26,008
The headline will be,
"How Far Will the Chaebol Heir Fall?"

844
00:48:26,926 --> 00:48:29,220
"Drunk Hit-and-Run with a Mysterious Woman

845
00:48:29,303 --> 00:48:30,804
During a Business Trip."

846
00:48:30,888 --> 00:48:32,097
When should we start?

847
00:48:32,181 --> 00:48:35,476
Let's shoot him down
when he reaches the apex.

848
00:48:35,559 --> 00:48:36,685
D-Day should be…

849
00:48:37,394 --> 00:48:39,647
a week after the launch.

850
00:48:50,616 --> 00:48:53,202
<i>Beauty that transcends time.</i>

851
00:49:08,384 --> 00:49:10,761
<i>Fragrance that captivates your attention.</i>

852
00:49:13,847 --> 00:49:16,267
<i>The single breath of fresh air</i>

853
00:49:17,142 --> 00:49:18,686
<i>in this desolate world.</i>

854
00:49:20,437 --> 00:49:22,189
<i>Dynaestie.</i>

855
00:49:45,129 --> 00:49:48,007
The market response has been great
since the first week of launch.

856
00:49:48,090 --> 00:49:50,551
We surpassed our sales target
in just one week,

857
00:49:50,634 --> 00:49:54,722
so we're running the new production lines
at full capacity to meet the demand.

858
00:49:54,805 --> 00:49:58,183
Ensure the national distribution network
runs smoothly without any issues.

859
00:49:58,267 --> 00:49:59,518
Yes, sir.

860
00:50:09,945 --> 00:50:11,280
No, I'm telling you, I saw her.

861
00:50:11,363 --> 00:50:13,365
-There was even a cosmetics ad.
-It can't be her.

862
00:50:13,449 --> 00:50:15,034
Even with the power of makeup…

863
00:50:15,117 --> 00:50:17,411
-Forget it. Let me just ask her.
-What?

864
00:50:18,412 --> 00:50:19,830
Excuse me.

865
00:50:19,913 --> 00:50:21,874
Have you ever shot a commercial?

866
00:50:21,957 --> 00:50:23,208
Like a cosmetics ad?

867
00:50:23,292 --> 00:50:25,586
For a brand called Dynaestie.

868
00:50:25,669 --> 00:50:27,796
Must I answer every single question?

869
00:50:28,797 --> 00:50:31,133
See? Would she really be
hanging laundry here if it were her?

870
00:50:31,216 --> 00:50:32,635
She'd be throwing a party somewhere.

871
00:50:32,718 --> 00:50:34,762
But it looks so much like her.

872
00:50:34,845 --> 00:50:36,680
Let me show you.
I'll show you downstairs.

873
00:50:36,764 --> 00:50:39,350
-What's up with her today?
-I'm telling you, it's her!

874
00:50:44,605 --> 00:50:46,357
MS. SHIN SEO-RI
WE WISH YOU A HAPPY BIRTHDAY

875
00:50:53,572 --> 00:50:55,324
Pick out some good ones for me.

876
00:50:55,407 --> 00:50:56,575
It's my grandkid's birthday.

877
00:50:56,659 --> 00:50:58,077
That's the best one.

878
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,871
Just give me 20,000 won for everything.

879
00:51:00,954 --> 00:51:03,457
What do you mean?
I already paid for the seaweed.

880
00:51:03,540 --> 00:51:04,500
Ma'am,

881
00:51:04,583 --> 00:51:06,168
I didn't get anything from you.

882
00:51:06,251 --> 00:51:07,961
You didn't give me anything yet.

883
00:51:08,545 --> 00:51:09,672
Are you kidding me?

884
00:51:09,755 --> 00:51:11,757
I paid for the seaweed already!

885
00:51:12,424 --> 00:51:15,177
Ma'am, I've been watching,
and you haven't paid yet.

886
00:51:15,803 --> 00:51:17,471
You must be confused.

887
00:51:17,554 --> 00:51:19,181
Are you buying seaweed again?

888
00:51:19,264 --> 00:51:22,559
You bought a whole bunch from me
just the other day.

889
00:51:43,038 --> 00:51:44,707
-Oh my God!
-Goodness! Ma'am!

890
00:51:44,790 --> 00:51:47,251
-What's wrong with her?
-Ma'am!

891
00:51:47,334 --> 00:51:49,169
-Please wake up!
-Ma'am!

892
00:51:49,253 --> 00:51:51,380
-Please wake up!
-Please wake up!

893
00:51:52,339 --> 00:51:54,842
<i>Ms. Shin Seo-ri?</i>
<i>Guardian of Ms. Nam Ok-sun?</i>

894
00:51:54,925 --> 00:51:58,303
<i>I'm calling from Songjin General Hospital.</i>
<i>You need to come quickly.</i>

895
00:52:00,222 --> 00:52:02,433
I'm about to lose it.
Where did he go after the meeting?

896
00:52:02,516 --> 00:52:04,727
-Without a word.
<i>-The number you are dialing…</i>

897
00:52:06,103 --> 00:52:07,479
-Ms. Kim!
-Yes?

898
00:52:07,563 --> 00:52:09,398
<i>-The number you are dialing…</i>
-I can't reach him.

899
00:52:09,481 --> 00:52:11,734
He stepped out for a moment.
He said he'd be right back.

900
00:52:11,817 --> 00:52:14,319
We're in trouble.
He might run into the reporters.

901
00:52:14,403 --> 00:52:16,363
-It's Cha Se-gye!
-There!

902
00:52:19,575 --> 00:52:21,994
Mr. Cha, did you drive
under the influence?

903
00:52:22,077 --> 00:52:24,496
We received a tip
that you drove drunk in Jeju.

904
00:52:24,580 --> 00:52:25,956
Who was your companion?

905
00:52:26,039 --> 00:52:29,585
Would you care to comment
on the nearby hit-and-run incident?

906
00:52:29,668 --> 00:52:31,462
-Please respond.
-What say you?

907
00:52:31,545 --> 00:52:33,589
I'll assess and issue
a statement later this afternoon.

908
00:52:33,672 --> 00:52:35,841
Are you admitting to driving drunk?

909
00:52:38,260 --> 00:52:39,845
<i>Who says I'm scared?</i>

910
00:52:39,928 --> 00:52:41,096
BIOJEI CEO CHA DRIVES DRUNK

911
00:52:41,221 --> 00:52:42,431
HIT-AND-RUN ALLEGATIONS SPREAD

912
00:52:44,224 --> 00:52:45,225
<i>Come on.</i>

913
00:52:58,280 --> 00:52:59,948
That's the narrative they came up with?

914
00:53:00,032 --> 00:53:01,492
Do people actually believe this?

915
00:53:01,575 --> 00:53:03,660
The press will piece together
any narrative that sells.

916
00:53:03,744 --> 00:53:06,914
A hit-and-run happened nearby
where there are no cameras.

917
00:53:06,997 --> 00:53:10,375
They're baselessly pinning it on you
and demanding an alibi.

918
00:53:10,459 --> 00:53:12,377
The stock price is already plummeting

919
00:53:12,461 --> 00:53:13,837
to 59,000 won.

920
00:53:16,799 --> 00:53:18,467
Defending our stock price comes first.

921
00:53:18,550 --> 00:53:21,303
We should call Ms. Shin as a witness--

922
00:53:21,386 --> 00:53:22,846
No, absolutely not.

923
00:53:22,930 --> 00:53:26,016
Do what you must to keep her
out of the press.

924
00:53:40,614 --> 00:53:42,407
<i>It's a cardioembolic stroke.</i>

925
00:53:43,033 --> 00:53:44,034
<i>It looks mild,</i>

926
00:53:44,117 --> 00:53:46,203
<i>but we also suspect Alzheimer's symptoms.</i>

927
00:53:46,787 --> 00:53:49,039
<i>Let's run some detailed tests first.</i>

928
00:53:50,833 --> 00:53:53,001
I haven't had much of an appetite lately.

929
00:53:53,669 --> 00:53:55,337
I just haven't been eating well.

930
00:53:57,673 --> 00:53:59,633
Did I scare you?

931
00:54:00,342 --> 00:54:03,679
Why did they even call you? Jeez.

932
00:54:03,762 --> 00:54:05,889
You need to eat properly.

933
00:54:06,890 --> 00:54:08,976
No wonder you keep passing out.

934
00:54:11,562 --> 00:54:12,521
I'm sorry.

935
00:54:12,604 --> 00:54:14,857
I'm a terrible grandma.

936
00:54:14,940 --> 00:54:18,193
I couldn't even make seaweed soup
for my granddaughter's birthday.

937
00:54:18,277 --> 00:54:19,820
Who cares about seaweed soup?

938
00:54:19,903 --> 00:54:21,488
Don't be like that, Seo-ri.

939
00:54:22,447 --> 00:54:24,449
Now that I've lived this long,

940
00:54:25,075 --> 00:54:27,411
I see there's a reason
we look out for others.

941
00:54:27,494 --> 00:54:31,456
Seaweed soup on your birthday,
rice cake soup on New Year's.

942
00:54:31,540 --> 00:54:35,252
You need to eat the right food
for every occasion.

943
00:54:35,335 --> 00:54:37,713
That's what brings small joys.

944
00:54:39,172 --> 00:54:41,216
Happiness doesn't accrue interest.

945
00:54:41,300 --> 00:54:43,302
You have to enjoy it when you can.

946
00:54:43,385 --> 00:54:44,636
Am I right or wrong?

947
00:54:46,013 --> 00:54:47,180
You are right.

948
00:55:01,653 --> 00:55:02,988
Seo-ri,

949
00:55:04,364 --> 00:55:06,825
do you know why your name is Seo-ri?

950
00:55:08,493 --> 00:55:10,412
My life was withered and hollow,

951
00:55:10,495 --> 00:55:12,247
but then you were born.

952
00:55:12,331 --> 00:55:14,374
To me, you were like a miracle.

953
00:55:14,458 --> 00:55:18,295
You were miraculously beautiful,
like a pure white frost flower.

954
00:55:19,004 --> 00:55:20,839
That's why I named you after one, Seo-ri.

955
00:55:24,426 --> 00:55:26,637
So don't go through your life

956
00:55:26,720 --> 00:55:29,348
lamenting like a fool.

957
00:55:29,431 --> 00:55:32,392
Be like the frost flowers that fall
in the height of summer.

958
00:55:33,852 --> 00:55:35,896
And fly freely, Seo-ri.

959
00:55:36,939 --> 00:55:38,065
Okay?

960
00:55:58,335 --> 00:55:59,962
Oh, my sweet baby.

961
00:56:01,004 --> 00:56:02,547
My sweet girl.

962
00:56:05,258 --> 00:56:06,218
Goodness.

963
00:56:16,311 --> 00:56:17,437
<i>Listen to me, Seo-ri.</i>

964
00:56:18,105 --> 00:56:21,483
<i>Just forget everything</i>
<i>that happened in the past.</i>

965
00:56:21,566 --> 00:56:23,110
<i>And just be happy.</i>

966
00:56:23,193 --> 00:56:26,363
<i>Just take no more than what is yours.</i>

967
00:56:29,116 --> 00:56:30,826
<i>I don't believe</i>

968
00:56:30,909 --> 00:56:33,662
<i>in happiness or miracles.</i>

969
00:56:34,579 --> 00:56:36,999
<i>Because there is no god who would grant</i>

970
00:56:37,082 --> 00:56:39,042
<i>the wishes of an impostor.</i>

971
00:56:39,126 --> 00:56:41,253
<i>Biojei CEO Cha Se-gye</i>

972
00:56:41,336 --> 00:56:44,131
<i>is embroiled</i>
<i>in a drunk-driving controversy.</i>

973
00:56:44,214 --> 00:56:46,466
<i>With allegations surfacing</i>
<i>that it may be linked</i>

974
00:56:46,550 --> 00:56:49,386
<i>to a hit-and-run accident</i>
<i>in the same area,</i>

975
00:56:49,469 --> 00:56:51,179
<i>-the public backlash against him…</i>
-Yes, sure.

976
00:56:51,263 --> 00:56:52,264
Understood.

977
00:56:52,347 --> 00:56:54,558
Yes, I'll be sure to get back to you.

978
00:56:55,684 --> 00:56:57,185
Yes, Reporter Kang.

979
00:56:57,269 --> 00:56:59,271
No, there was no hit-and-run. Right.

980
00:56:59,354 --> 00:57:01,106
And it wasn't drunk driving either.

981
00:57:07,571 --> 00:57:08,488
CHAIRMAN

982
00:57:11,450 --> 00:57:14,703
Mr. Son, what is going on?
Did he really drive drunk?

983
00:57:14,786 --> 00:57:16,038
Grandfather, it's me.

984
00:57:16,121 --> 00:57:18,081
-I was not drunk.
-Then what's with the video?

985
00:57:18,165 --> 00:57:19,875
A woman and a hit-and-run?

986
00:57:19,958 --> 00:57:22,169
You'll be cleared
if you just prove your alibi.

987
00:57:22,794 --> 00:57:24,963
I'll take care of it all, so don't worry.

988
00:57:28,008 --> 00:57:29,718
Sir, please don't do this.

989
00:57:29,801 --> 00:57:31,303
Let's call Ms. Shin now.

990
00:57:31,386 --> 00:57:32,554
This could be disastrous.

991
00:57:32,637 --> 00:57:34,222
Enough of that now.

992
00:57:35,057 --> 00:57:36,975
One scapegoat is enough.

993
00:57:40,937 --> 00:57:42,314
<i>Biojei CEO Cha Se-gye</i>

994
00:57:42,397 --> 00:57:44,816
<i>is facing controversy</i>
<i>over a suspected DUI.</i>

995
00:57:44,900 --> 00:57:46,193
<i>CCTV footage of him driving drunk</i>

996
00:57:46,276 --> 00:57:48,945
<i>during a recent trip to Jeju</i>
<i>has just been released.</i>

997
00:57:49,029 --> 00:57:51,323
<i>With a hit-and-run on a nearby road,</i>

998
00:57:51,406 --> 00:57:53,450
<i>suspicions of a connection are growing.</i>

999
00:57:53,533 --> 00:57:56,036
<i>Questions are also mounting</i>
<i>about the woman</i>

1000
00:57:56,119 --> 00:57:57,871
<i>who accompanied him in the car.</i>

1001
00:57:57,954 --> 00:57:59,623
-Cha Se-gye?
-Unbelievable.

1002
00:57:59,706 --> 00:58:01,875
The news just gives you
a headache nowadays.

1003
00:58:01,958 --> 00:58:05,378
Guys like him should rot
in prison for the rest of their lives.

1004
00:58:05,462 --> 00:58:06,713
Prison?

1005
00:58:06,797 --> 00:58:09,216
Then again, prison is nothing to them.

1006
00:58:09,299 --> 00:58:11,551
Getting drunk and picking up women.

1007
00:58:11,635 --> 00:58:14,763
I'm sure he'll just use
his connections to get out.

1008
00:58:14,846 --> 00:58:16,098
Don't you think?

1009
00:58:21,311 --> 00:58:23,688
There she is. Finally.

1010
00:58:30,487 --> 00:58:32,989
Where were you with your phone off?

1011
00:58:33,073 --> 00:58:34,783
We're in big trouble right now.

1012
00:58:34,866 --> 00:58:37,953
-Are you talking about Cha Se-gye?
-You already know.

1013
00:58:38,036 --> 00:58:40,247
You might get dragged into this,

1014
00:58:40,330 --> 00:58:43,208
so Ms. Hong said not to answer
any unknown numbers.

1015
00:58:43,708 --> 00:58:45,377
What do I have to do with him?

1016
00:58:48,630 --> 00:58:49,631
But,

1017
00:58:50,382 --> 00:58:51,883
he will not end up in prison, right?

1018
00:58:51,967 --> 00:58:53,343
He did not even drink.

1019
00:58:53,426 --> 00:58:55,345
Who knows? Real or not,

1020
00:58:55,428 --> 00:58:58,140
the public has already written him off.

1021
00:58:59,975 --> 00:59:01,643
He has his grandfather and loyal subjects.

1022
00:59:01,726 --> 00:59:03,854
Plenty of people can protect him.

1023
00:59:03,937 --> 00:59:05,564
<i>But you…</i>

1024
00:59:05,647 --> 00:59:08,650
<i>What exactly can you do for him?</i>

1025
00:59:11,862 --> 00:59:13,196
Nothing will happen.

1026
00:59:15,949 --> 00:59:17,993
Hey, Rooftop, are you just getting back?

1027
00:59:18,076 --> 00:59:20,078
Gwang-nam kept calling you.

1028
00:59:20,162 --> 00:59:21,538
I just saw him.

1029
00:59:22,247 --> 00:59:25,041
Manager Gu, it looks like
you are working hard again today.

1030
00:59:31,131 --> 00:59:32,841
All thanks to Rooftop,

1031
00:59:32,924 --> 00:59:35,719
the lights are working again. It's nice.

1032
01:00:47,791 --> 01:00:50,210
<i>Shin Seo-ri, you're one wicked brat,</i>

1033
01:00:50,293 --> 01:00:52,295
<i>but I'll let it slide for your birthday.</i>

1034
01:00:52,837 --> 01:00:55,131
<i>Even if you hurt me</i>
<i>and push me away with hurtful words,</i>

1035
01:00:55,215 --> 01:00:57,634
<i>I should still wish you happiness.</i>

1036
01:01:04,140 --> 01:01:05,183
No.

1037
01:01:05,934 --> 01:01:07,936
I tell you, I am an impostor.

1038
01:01:11,564 --> 01:01:13,275
<i>May your night shine</i>

1039
01:01:13,358 --> 01:01:16,903
<i>a little brighter than yesterday.</i>

1040
01:01:25,829 --> 01:01:27,747
<i>Why do you keep making me waver?</i>

1041
01:01:31,835 --> 01:01:34,170
<i>I just want to stay still and quiet.</i>

1042
01:01:35,005 --> 01:01:37,090
<i>Why do you make me sway?</i>

1043
01:01:39,217 --> 01:01:41,428
<i>If you keep making me waver,</i>

1044
01:01:42,262 --> 01:01:43,513
<i>I…</i>

1045
01:01:44,222 --> 01:01:46,975
I will shamelessly start hoping for more.

1046
01:01:50,478 --> 01:01:52,522
Maybe happiness and miracles…

1047
01:01:54,733 --> 01:01:57,027
are within my reach.

1048
01:02:01,239 --> 01:02:03,700
Maybe I do not want to be alone anymore.

1049
01:02:06,828 --> 01:02:08,788
That is what I end up hoping for.

1050
01:02:18,048 --> 01:02:19,215
<i>Seo-ri.</i>

1051
01:02:20,175 --> 01:02:22,510
<i>My beautiful granddaughter.</i>

1052
01:02:22,594 --> 01:02:25,347
<i>Your grandma prays every single night.</i>

1053
01:02:26,139 --> 01:02:29,059
<i>Praying for you to meet someone</i>

1054
01:02:29,142 --> 01:02:31,644
<i>who can melt your frozen heart.</i>

1055
01:02:32,645 --> 01:02:35,357
That's my one wish.

1056
01:02:35,440 --> 01:02:37,400
A wish I want to see come true.

1057
01:02:38,526 --> 01:02:40,278
My last wish.

1058
01:03:16,606 --> 01:03:17,649
Why are you here?

1059
01:03:19,234 --> 01:03:20,318
To protect you.

1060
01:03:23,863 --> 01:03:24,906
Have you lost your mind?

1061
01:03:25,573 --> 01:03:26,825
I also want to try.

1062
01:03:27,617 --> 01:03:29,202
Whatever it may be. For you.

1063
01:03:33,498 --> 01:03:35,083
Hey, who's that woman?

1064
01:03:42,507 --> 01:03:44,300
What do you think you're doing?

1065
01:03:47,137 --> 01:03:48,721
Protecting you.

1066
01:03:50,223 --> 01:03:51,975
I gave you my word.

1067
01:03:54,436 --> 01:03:56,271
You sure this is protecting me?

1068
01:03:56,354 --> 01:03:58,022
Or are we just going down together?

1069
01:04:10,410 --> 01:04:11,494
<i>If we are ruined,</i>

1070
01:04:11,578 --> 01:04:13,079
<i>let us embrace it.</i>

1071
01:04:13,830 --> 01:04:16,666
<i>If we are broken, let us embrace it.</i>

1072
01:04:17,917 --> 01:04:19,210
It is fine

1073
01:04:20,128 --> 01:04:21,087
if we are together.

1074
01:04:24,174 --> 01:04:25,341
What…

1075
01:04:26,843 --> 01:04:28,094
are you doing?

1076
01:04:28,970 --> 01:04:29,971
<i>May your night shine…</i>

1077
01:04:34,767 --> 01:04:38,146
<i>a little brighter than yesterday.</i>

1078
01:04:39,272 --> 01:04:40,899
It really is shining.

1079
01:04:44,110 --> 01:04:45,570
Now that I am with you.

1080
01:05:33,535 --> 01:05:36,913
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1081
01:06:07,610 --> 01:06:09,362
I shall hereby grant you my permission.

1082
01:06:09,445 --> 01:06:10,613
You want to see each other?

1083
01:06:10,697 --> 01:06:13,283
<i>-How about </i>ramyeon<i> for round two?</i>
-I am not ready for this step yet!

1084
01:06:13,366 --> 01:06:14,242
Watch your hands!

1085
01:06:14,325 --> 01:06:16,828
<i>Ms. Shin, you should leave now.</i>

1086
01:06:16,911 --> 01:06:18,830
<i>I'd like for you to get lost now.</i>

1087
01:06:18,913 --> 01:06:20,748
How dare you cheat on me?

1088
01:06:21,374 --> 01:06:23,835
You have two weeks. Destruction deadline.

1089
01:06:23,918 --> 01:06:27,213
<i>It appears I am fated</i>
<i>to curse the men around me.</i>

1090
01:06:27,964 --> 01:06:29,090
<i>What is this?</i>

1091
01:06:30,592 --> 01:06:32,135
<i>Who are you?</i>

1092
01:06:32,218 --> 01:06:34,262
Who are you really?

1093
01:06:38,391 --> 01:06:40,393
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

